Subject: [PATCH] Utils/Allocator: tolerate missing procfs instead of spinning

BuildKit's architecture probe (util/archutil, run by dockerd on every
ListWorkers/build) executes the guest binary chroot'd into an empty temp
dir: no /proc, no /dev, nothing but the probe ELF. Under the binfmt_misc
registration that lands FEX in three release-mode defects that compound
into an infinite loop:

1. StealMemoryRegion's open("/proc/self/maps") fails, but the failure
   assert (LogMan::Throw::AFmt) is a no-op in release builds, so the dead
   fd (-1) flows into CollectMemoryGaps.
2. CollectMemoryGaps' EOF check compares the ssize_t read() result against
   `sizeof(Buffer) - PendingBytes`: -1 promotes to SIZE_MAX, the EOF path
   never triggers, and the loop keeps issuing read(-1) with drifting
   negative offsets forever (state R, one core pegged).
3. The probe process never exits; buildkit has no timeout and caches the
   probe under a sync.Once, wedging dockerd's whole BuildKit Control API
   (every `docker build`/`buildx` call hangs silently). ArcBox ABX-494.

Fix, in layers: make the EOF check signed, retry EINTR, and treat hard
read errors as EOF (kills the spin class); return an empty region list
when procfs is absent; and have Setup48BitAllocatorIfExists skip allocator
creation in that case — the same degraded configuration as a sub-48-bit-VA
host — so the probe runs the guest binary and exits normally.

diff --git a/FEXCore/Source/Utils/Allocator.cpp b/FEXCore/Source/Utils/Allocator.cpp
index 3d9944a..6519149 100644
--- a/FEXCore/Source/Utils/Allocator.cpp
+++ b/FEXCore/Source/Utils/Allocator.cpp
@@ -179,12 +179,22 @@ fextl::vector<MemoryRegion> CollectMemoryGaps(uintptr_t Begin, uintptr_t End, in
       auto PendingBytes = Remaining;
       do {
         Remaining = read(MapsFD, Buffer + PendingBytes, sizeof(Buffer) - PendingBytes);
-      } while (Remaining == -1 && errno == EAGAIN);
-
-      if (Remaining < sizeof(Buffer) - PendingBytes) {
+        // Retry a delivered signal (EINTR) as well as EAGAIN: a bare -1 falls
+        // through to the EOF clamp below, so ending the loop on EINTR would
+        // parse a partial /proc/self/maps snapshot. Only a hard error or a
+        // genuine short read should end the scan.
+      } while (Remaining == -1 && (errno == EAGAIN || errno == EINTR));
+
+      // Signed comparison: a failed read returns -1, and letting it promote
+      // to size_t would skip the EOF path and spin on the dead fd forever.
+      if (Remaining < static_cast<ssize_t>(sizeof(Buffer)) - PendingBytes) {
         EndOfFileReached = true;
       }

+      // Treat hard read errors as EOF: parse whatever was buffered, never
+      // walk the cursor backwards through negative byte counts.
+      Remaining = std::max<ssize_t>(Remaining, 0);
+
       Remaining += PendingBytes;

       Cursor = Buffer;
@@ -228,6 +238,13 @@ fextl::vector<MemoryRegion> StealMemoryRegion(uintptr_t Begin, uintptr_t End) {

   const int MapsFD = open("/proc/self/maps", O_RDONLY);
   LogMan::Throw::AFmt(MapsFD != -1, "Failed to open /proc/self/maps");
+  if (MapsFD == -1) {
+    // procfs is unavailable (e.g. exec'd inside a bare chroot sandbox such
+    // as BuildKit's architecture probe). The memory map is unknowable, so
+    // there is nothing safe to steal — release builds must degrade instead
+    // of dereferencing a dead fd.
+    return {};
+  }

   auto Regions = CollectMemoryGaps(Begin, End, MapsFD);
   close(MapsFD);
@@ -291,6 +308,13 @@ fextl::vector<MemoryRegion> Setup48BitAllocatorIfExists(size_t PageSize) {
   uintptr_t Begin48BitVA = 0x0'8000'0000'0000ULL;
   uintptr_t End48BitVA = 0x1'0000'0000'0000ULL;
   auto Regions = StealMemoryRegion(Begin48BitVA, End48BitVA);
+  if (Regions.empty()) {
+    // /proc/self/maps was unreadable (bare chroot sandbox): without the map
+    // there is no region list to feed the 64-bit allocator. Run without the
+    // 48-bit reservation — the same configuration as a sub-48-bit-VA host —
+    // rather than building an allocator with nothing to allocate from.
+    return {};
+  }

   Alloc64 = Alloc::OSAllocator::Create64BitAllocatorWithRegions(Regions);
   AssignHookOverrides(PageSize);
